        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals134"/>
        <p><a href="ch73s36.html#MonstersAnimals133">Rats</a> usually run away. They bite only as a last resort.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2308910"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals135"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> <a href="ch73s36.html#MonstersAnimals133">Rats</a> have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills179">Hide</a> and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills211">Move Silently</a> checks, and a +8 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills55">Balance</a>, <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills71">Climb</a>, and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> checks. A <a href="ch73s36.html#MonstersAnimals133">rat</a> can always choose to take 10 on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills71">Climb</a> checks, even if rushed or threatened. A <a href="ch73s36.html#MonstersAnimals133">rat</a> uses its Dexterity modifier instead of its Strength modifier for <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills71">Climb</a> and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> checks. A <a href="ch73s36.html#MonstersAnimals133">rat</a> has a +8 racial bonus on any <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> check to perform some special action or avoid a hazard. It can always choose to take 10 on a <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> check, even if distracted or endangered. It can use the run action while swimming, provided it swims in a straight line.</p>
